Color Walk - A GTK+ comicbook reader written in Python


Description
-----------
Color Walk is designed to be easy on the eyes, fast, and uncomplicated.

Color Walk is released under the GNU General Public License (GPL)
version 2, see the file 'COPYING' for more information.


Getting it
----------
The latest stable version can always be found here:
 
http://members.shaw.ca/davekeogh/colorwalk/

The very latest, possibly broken version, can checked out from the 
project's git repository:

 $ git clone git://github.com/davekeogh/colorwalk.git


Installing
----------
Color Walk requires Python 2.4 and the GTK+ 2.2.x bindings.

Simple install procedure:

 $ tar xzvf colorwalk-x.x.x.tar.gz		# Unpack the sources
 $ cd colorwalk-x.x.x					# Move to the source directory
 [ Become root if necessary ]
 # python setup.py						# Install Color Walk
